Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Development Engineer* position with *Amazon*. I bring over three years of professional experience building large-scale distributed services, production AI agents, retrieval and indexing platforms, and evaluation infrastructure, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY (GPA 4.0/4.0).

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered systems that closely match the technical depth required by Amazon Advertising's Autonomous Development team. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and operated large-scale distributed services for production AI agents and developer-intelligence systems using Python, LangGraph, LangChain, and FastAPI, serving 10,000+ users through 40+ specialized sub-agents with secure access control. I also built agentic code-generation systems for autonomous software delivery by integrating OpenAI Codex with a custom Bitbucket MCP server, turning engineering intake into reviewed code changes and automating PR triage across 25-30 PRs per week. To keep agents grounded and measurable, I built retrieval and indexing platforms with LlamaIndex, OpenAI embeddings, and Pgvector, and wired GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines to OpenTelemetry trace-based evaluation frameworks that checked agent correctness across code reviews, source control management, build processes, testing, and operations.

Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I built backend and data systems with the reliability and scaling focus this role requires. I designed Java and Spring Boot distributed services with PostgreSQL and Redis to handle file uploads, downloads, and deletions across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO through API design patterns for reliability and scaling. I also optimized large-scale data and retrieval paths in PostgreSQL, improved query latency for business stakeholders through React visualizations, and owned operational excellence for 100K+ weekly executions with AWS Step Functions by reducing Lambda timeouts and improving error recovery, cost control, and 24/7 operations. My Dark Factory project extends the same story into LLM orchestration: it coordinates dependency-aware task DAGs across multi-machine AI agents with retries, timeout handling, failure recovery, and quality checks before production-ready code changes.

Amazon's mission to make customers' lives better and easier every day by relentlessly inventing on their behalf, together with Leadership Principles such as Customer Obsession, Ownership, Invent and Simplify, and Insist on the Highest Standards, is directly aligned with the way I build. The Autonomous Development team's mission to make autonomous software delivery correct, safe, and scalable at Amazon scale is the kind of high-ownership engineering challenge I want to work on. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

